=== EXAMPLE: scdoc_Overviews_Operators_ex43 ===

DESCRIPTION: A very_dark pure_tone sound, with complex oscillator character around 441 Hz, featuring slow attack and dynamic envelope, with chaotic spectral movement, filtered with resonant_steep_rolloff character, and spectrally simple.

CATEGORIES:
  attack_time: slow
  brightness: very_dark
  crest_factor_db: dynamic
  envelope_flatness: sustained
  harmonic_to_noise_ratio: pure_tone
  spectral_complexity_mean: simple
  spectral_flux_normalized: chaotic
  spectral_slope: steep_rolloff
  temporal_centroid: balanced

SYNTHESIS CONCEPTS (key values):
[oscillator]
  fundamental_freq: 441.2715
  harmonic_decay_rate: -14.2267
  harmonic_regularity: 0.5013
  pitch_clarity: 141.6143
  inharmonicity: 0.0011
  type: complex
[filter]
  spectral_slope: -4.7564
  resonance_freq: 430.6641

SUPERCOLLIDER CODE:
// Title: Operators Example 43
// Author: SC Documentation
// URL: http://doc.sccode.org/Overviews/Operators.html
// Tags: Operators, Overviews
// ---
// --- Example 43 ---
(
{ // creates a rhythm
var mul = 0.2 absdif: FSinOsc.ar(2, 0, 0.5);
FSinOsc.ar(440, 0, mul);
}.play;
)
